'''Margit Papp''' (born 30 April 1948) is a [[Hungary|Hungarian]] former [[Athletics (sport)|athlete]]. She competed in the [[Summer Olympic Games]] in [[1972 Summer Olympics|1972]], [[1976 Summer Olympics|1976]] and [[1980 Summer Olympics|1980]] and won the gold medal in women's [[Pentathlon#Modern Olympics|pentathlon]] at the [[1978 European Athletics Championships|1978 European Championships]].

==Career==

Papp first competed in the [[European Athletics Championships|European Championships]] in [[1966 European Athletics Championships|Budapest 1966]] as an 18-year-old, placing 18th in the pentathlon.<ref name="tp">{{tilastopaja|id=42128|sex=w}}</ref> She made her Olympic debut in [[Munich]] in [[Athletics at the 1972 Summer Olympics – Women's pentathlon|1972]], finishing 23rd with 4074 points.<ref name="tp"/><ref name="sr">{{cite web |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/pa/margit-papp-1.html |title=Margit Papp Bio, Stats and Results |accessdate=30 April 2014 |publisher=Sports Reference LLC}}</ref> Four years later in [[Montréal]] she scored 4535 points and placed 8th.<ref name="sr"/>

At the [[1978 European Athletics Championships|1978 European Championships]] in [[Prague]] Papp scored 4655 points and won the gold medal.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.gbrathletics.com/ic/ecw.htm |title=European Championships (Women) |publisher=''[[Athletics Weekly]]'' |accessdate=30 April 2014}}</ref> She originally placed second behind the defending champion, [[Nadezhda Tkachenko]] of the [[Soviet Union]], but moved up when Tkachenko was disqualified for [[Doping in sport|doping]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/summer/1980/ATH/womens-pentathlon.html |title=Athletics at the 1980 Moskva Summer Games: Women's Pentathlon |publisher=Sports Reference LLC |accessdate=30 April 2014}}</ref> Papp made a final Olympic appearance in 1980, placing fifth with 4562 points.<ref name="sr"/> In the 1978 European Championships and the 1980 Olympics she also competed in the [[long jump]], failing to qualify for the final on either occasion.<ref name="tp"/>

